The fact that jobless levels for Black Americans are higher than Whites by the end of 2021 unfortunately came as no surprise. With U.S. COVID-19 deaths at global highs and monetary policy tightening looming, should there be worries that this persistent employment gap would grow further? In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michael Wang argues that the U.S. perhaps should be addressing the rights for equal opportunities to gainful employment at home first, before lecturing other countries about human rights.